videoSnippet.title: World Champions Collide! || Carlsen vs Abdusattorov! || FIDE World Rapid Championship (2022)
videoSnippet.description:
Abdusattorov vs Carlsen 2021 HERE! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8d8bUgICOEw

Photos by Lenart Ootes
Have a great day :)

Carlsen, Magnus (2834) - Abdusattorov, Nodirbek (2676)
FIDE World Rapid Championship (chess24.com) [4] 2022.12.26
A01 Nimzovich-Larsen attack, modern variation

1.b3 e5 2.Bb2 Nc6 3.e3 Nf6 4.Nf3 Bd6 5.c4 O-O 6.d3 Re8 7.a3 a5 8.Be2 Bf8 9.O-O d5 10.cxd5 Nxd5 11.Nbd2 f6 12.Qc2 Bf5 13.Rfe1 Bg6 14.g4 Qd7 15.Kh1 Rad8 16.Ne4 Kh8 17.Rad1 Bf7 18.Rg1 Nb6 19.Rg3 a4 20.bxa4 Na5 21.Rdg1 Bd5 22.g5 f5 23.Nc3 Bc6 24.e4 Nxa4 25.Nxa4 Bxa4 26.Qc3 Nc6 27.g6 Nd4 28.Ng5 Nxe2 29.Nf7+ Qxf7 30.gxf7 Nxc3 31.fxe8=Q Bxe8 32.Bxc3 Bg6 33.exf5 Bxf5 34.Bxe5 Bxd3 35.Rxg7

00:00 Hello Everyone!
00:45 Game Starts!
01:25 Completely New Game!
07:55 Pause the video!
11:25 It was In This Position!
13:30 Contributions!

The FIDE Women's World Rapid Championship is an 11-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $150,000, with a $40,000 top prize.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com
